This paper is primarily focused on face recognition, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The paper also proposes a new method for sparsifying neural network connections, which is a topic of interest in machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed method in terms of model size and computational efficiency, which could be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) applications.
